<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,295,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">
This species was recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[485,530,296,322]" name="Iran" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[582,737,295,321]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Iwan, D. &amp; Lobl, I. &amp; Bouchard, P. &amp; Bousquet, Y. &amp; Kaminski, M. J. &amp; Merkl, O. &amp; Ando, K. &amp; Schawaller, W." box="[776,974,295,322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="121" pagination="1802" refId="ref10643" refString="Iwan, D., Lobl, I., Bouchard, P., Bousquet, Y., Kaminski, M. J., Merkl, O., Ando, K. &amp; Schawaller, W. (2020) Family Tenebrionidae Latreille, 1802. In: Iwan, D. &amp; Lobl, I. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 5. Tenebrionoidea. Leiden, Brill, pp. 104 - 475. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004434998" type="book chapter" year="2020">
Iwan 
<emphasis box="[838,886,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
but it is distributed only in Central Transcaucasia, 
<collectingCountry box="[257,358,331,357]" name="Armenia" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[368,458,331,357]" name="Georgia" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Georgia</collectingCountry>
and W 
<collectingCountry box="[539,662,331,357]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Abdurakhmanov, G. M. &amp; Nabozhenko, M. V." box="[675,1104,331,357]" pageId="16" pageNumber="121" refId="ref10125" refString="Abdurakhmanov, G. M. &amp; Nabozhenko, M. V. (2011) Keys and catalogue to darkling beetles (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae s. str.) of the Caucasus and south of European part of Russia. KMK Scientific Press Ltd, Moscow, 361 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="2011">Abdurakhmanov &amp; Nabozhenko 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nabozhenko, M. V. &amp; Kalashian, M. Yu. &amp; Mazmanyan, M. A." box="[1114,1382,331,358]" pageId="16" pageNumber="121" pagination="425 - 450" refId="ref10983" refString="Nabozhenko, M. V., Kalashian, M. Yu., Mazmanyan, M. A. (2021) A faunistic review of darkling beetles (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae; excluding Alleculinae) of Armenia and partly the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic of Azerbaijan with new records and taxonomic notes. Caucasian Entomological Bulletin, 17, 425 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.23885 / 181433262021172 - 425450" type="journal article" year="2021">
Nabozhenko 
<emphasis box="[1261,1309,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
). We studied also 
<specimenCount box="[293,448,367,394]" pageId="16" pageNumber="121" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
with the label “ 
<collectingRegion box="[628,706,367,393]" country="Turkey" name="Artvin" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Artvin</collectingRegion>
” (now town in 
<collectingCountry box="[882,964,367,394]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Turkey</collectingCountry>
) in HNHM. Thus, the species is recorded for the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[331,411,403,429]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="121">Turkey</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
